<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Parkinsonia</i> <i>microphylla</i> is co-dominant in the shrub or small tree canopy with <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>bigelovii</i>, <i>Encelia</i> <i>farinosa</i>, <i>Fagonia</i> <i>laevis</i>, <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i> and <i>Tetracoccus</i> <i>hallii</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Carnegiea</i> <i>gigantea</i> or <i>Olneya</i> <i>tesota</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs or small trees < 8 m; canopy is open to intermittent. Herbaceous layer is usually sparse, yet may have spectacular annual blooms. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Metavolcanic and sedimentary outcrops, mesas, foothill slopes, and washes. Soils are thin, often with a caliche layer.  </div>
</div>

		
